#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1537
msgid ""
"MetaModelica. - The debugger for algorithmic code is now available and "
"operational in Eclipse for debugging of MetaModelica programs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1541
msgid "OpenModelica 1.4.1, June 2006"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1543
msgid ""
"This release has only improvements and bug fixes of the OMC compiler, the"
" MDT plugin and the OMDev components. The OMShell and OMNotebook are the "
"same."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1553
msgid "Support for external objects. - OMC now reports the version number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1554
msgid ""
"(via command line switches or CORBA API getVersion()). - Implemented "
"caching for faster instantiation of large models. - Many bug fixes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1560
msgid ""
"Improvements of the error reporting when building the OMC compiler. The "
"errors are now added to the problems view. The latest MDT release is "
"version 0.6.6 (2006-06-06)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1567
msgid ""
"Small fixes in the MetaModelica compiler. MetaModelica Users Guide is now"
" part of the OMDev release. The latest OMDev was release in 2006-06-06."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1572
msgid "OpenModelica 1.4.0, May 2006"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1574
msgid ""
"This release has a number of improvements described below. The most "
"significant change is probably that OMC has now been translated to an "
"extended subset of Modelica (MetaModelica), and that all development of "
"the compiler is now done in this version.."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1585
msgid "Partial support for mixed system of equations. - New initialization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1586
msgid ""
"routine, based on optimization (minimizing residuals of initial "
"equations). - Symbolic simplification of builtin operators for vectors "
"and matrices. - Improved code generation in simulation code to support "
"e.g. Modelica functions. - Support for classes extending basic types, "
"e.g. connectors (support for MSL 2.2 block connectors). - Support for "
"parametric plotting via the plotParametric command. - Many bug fixes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1596
msgid ""
"Essentially the same OMShell as in 1.3.1. One difference is that now all "
"error messages are sent to the command window instead of to a separate "
"log window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1603
msgid ""
"Many significant improvements and bug fixes. This version supports "
"graphic plots within the cells in the notebook. Improved cell handling "
"and Modelica code syntax highlighting. Command completion of the most "
"common OMC commands is now supported. The notebook has been used in "
"several courses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1612
msgid ""
"This is the first really useful version of MDT. Full browsing of Modelica"
" code, e.g. the MSL 2.2, is now supported. (MetaModelica browsing is not "
"yet fully supported). Full support for automatic indentation of Modelica "
"code, including the MetaModelica extensions. Many bug fixes. The Eclipse "
"plug-in is now in use for OpenModelica development at PELAB and MathCore "
"Engineering AB since approximately one month."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1623 ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1690
msgid ""
"The following mechanisms have been put in place to support OpenModelica "
"development."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1626
msgid "A separate web page for OMDev (OpenModelica Development Environment)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1627
msgid "A pre-packaged OMDev zip-file with precompiled binaries for"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1628
msgid ""
"development under Windows using the mingw Gnu compiler from the Eclipse "
"MDT plug-in. (Development is also possible using Visual Studio). - All "
"source code of the OpenModelica compiler has recently been translated to "
"an extended subset of Modelica, currently called MetaModelica. The "
"current size of OMC is approximately 100 000 lines All development is now"
" done in this version. - A new tutorial and users guide for development "
"in MetaModelica. - Successful builds and tests of OMC under Linux and "
"Solaris."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1638
msgid "OpenModelica 1.3.1, November 2005"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1640
msgid "This release has several important highlights."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1642
msgid ""
"This is also the \\*first\\* release for which the New BSD (Berkeley) "
"open-source license applies to the source code, including the whole "
"compiler and run-time system. This makes is possible to use OpenModelica "
"for both academic and commercial purposes without restrictions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1650
msgid ""
"This release includes a significantly improved OpenModelica Compiler "
"(OMC):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1653
msgid "Support for hybrid and discrete-event simulation (if-equations,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1654
msgid ""
"if-expressions, when-equations; not yet if-statements and when-"
"statements). - Parsing of full Modelica 2.2 - Improved support for "
"external functions. - Vectorization of function arguments; each-"
"modifiers, better implementation of replaceable, better handling of "
"structural parameters, better support for vector and array operations, "
"and many other improvements. - Flattening of the Modelica Block library "
"version 1.5 (except a few models), and simulation of most of these. - "
"Automatic index reduction (present also in previous release). - Updated "
"User's Guide including examples of hybrid simulation and external "
"functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1668
msgid ""
"An improved window-based interactive command shell, now including command"
" completion and better editing and font size support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1674
msgid ""
"A free implementation of an OpenModelica notebook (OMNotebook), for "
"electronic books with course material, including the DrModelica "
"interactive course material. It is possible to simulate and plot from "
"this notebook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1682
msgid ""
"An early alpha version of the first Eclipse plug-in (called MDT for "
"Modelica Development Tooling) for Modelica Development. This version "
"gives compilation support and partial support for browsing Modelica "
"package hierarchies and classes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tracreleases.rst:1693
msgid "Bugzilla support for OpenModelica bug tracking, accessible to anybody."
msgstr ""

